An anonymous 4-star review on Yelp for an Indian restaurant doesn't appear to be negative at first glance. The diner compliments the naan bread, praises the butter chicken, and calls the Three Greens Saag "wonderful," though many of the descriptions make curious references to the dishes' laxative effects. It's not until the end that the reviewer gets explicit: "The meal was delectable, exotic, and incinerated everything in my intestines." Although he concludes that the food was delicious, he takes off a single star for pricey biryani
